[{"id":"04d2576e416273e9dc9734b31a5692c4","from":"J. Epstein","from_email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to":"LVJET@aol.com","to_list":[{"name":"LVJET@aol.com","email":"LVJET@aol.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"Re: G2 leather update:","date":"2007-05-09T11:41:43.000Z","formatted_date":"May 9, 2007","formatted_time":"11:41 AM","body":"please explain to eric, that the delay in fixing the interior, is costing me a great deal of time and dimunition in value of selling the plane. HE said he would stand behind the work and I expect him to do, so, he should check with his attnys if need be regarding responsibility. . It can't be mine. It is not my dissatisfaction.. it is obvious. to anyone. who sees it... WE await his proposal..\n\n\n----- Original Message ----\nFrom: \"LVJET@aol.com\" <LVJET@aol.com>\nTo: JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM\nCc: DKIESQ@aol.com; kellens@earthlink.net\nSent: Tuesday, May 8, 2007 10:04:13 PM\nSubject: G2 leather update:\n\n\nJeffrey, see Eric's comments below, \nI plan on taking the Gulfstream to Paint shop Friday after seats are removed.\nPaint shop is located in London, Ontario Canada, 1 hour north west of NYC.\nDarren, I thought you should be aware of current updates with Eric Roth at IJI on leather for Gulfstream.\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nSee what's free at AOL.com. \nDear Larry,\n \nLet me start off by saying that International Jet Interiors appreciated the relationship with JE & company.\n \nWe refurbished the GIIb using leather that JE had specified \u2013 not IJI.  The seating upholstery came out great and the problem that I agree exists is the \u201cpuckering\u201d of the leather while in St. Thomas .\n \nIt is my strong opinion that this problem is somehow due to the high humidity level interacting with the leather causing this adverse effect.\n \nThe seats looked great when we viewed them (post - St. Thomas ) at Teterboro , NJ .\n \nFurther, the one single seat that has not left our building also looks great \u2013 no puckering \u2013 even after we put sandbags on the seats for over three hours to create the weight of a passenger.\n \nWe have contacted and sent JE\u2019s photo\u2019s to Edeleman and have had numerous discussions with Kasthy \u2013 our Edelman representative.  She assured me that the owners of the company as well as may others who could be instrumental in identifying the cause of the problem have all viewed JE\u2019s photo\u2019s.\n \nEdeleman has about 100 sq. ft of this specific dye lot in stock and has sent it to the lab for testing.\n \nAt this point Edelman has made no suggestion as to what the problem is and if they agree that it may be their leather.\n \nAdditionally, if it is their leather, they have not expressed any terms of financial recourse.\n \nThe new leather that JE would like will take 2 weeks to manufacture.  The piping color is \u201cin stock\u201d in a different leather type, but one that Edelman believes would work well as it is only the trim.\n \nI want to make sure that we are very clear as to everyone\u2019s position at this point as you have requested for us to remove the seats without identifying who will be financially responsible in compensating IJI to perform any work as desired by JE.\n \nI will work on special pricing to show my contribution in trying to resolve JE\u2019s dissatisfaction.\n \nI look forward to speaking with you tomorrow morning at 9:00.  Hopefully by then Jay and Glenn will have had time to see if they have any weight and balance information on the GIIb to see if we removed the cabin single and double chairs, would the aircraft still fall within the envelope.\n \nWe are making a very sincere effort to keep JE happy.\n \n \nSincerely,\n \nEric H. Roth\nPresident\n \n\n \nInternational Jet Interiors\n960 South Second Street\nRonkonkoma, NY 11779\n631.737.5900   Phone\n631.7371249     Fax\n516.857.6533    Cell\n \neroth@intljet.com    e-mail\nwww.intljet.com       website\n\n\n\nFrom: LVJET@aol.com [mailto:LVJET@aol.com] \nSent: Tuesday, May 08, 2007 3:52 PM\nTo: ERoth@intljet.com\nCc: Jmassar@intljet.com; JETCARE@aol.com; jetcare@attglobal.net\nSubject: N909JE Hyperion Air Inc.\n \nHello Eric,\nI hope you had satisfactory conversation with Edleman leather.\nI am confirming that JEE does not want the current leather installed in G2.\nThis is the leather he would like installed:\nChair fully covered in: Cashmere Calf, Marble CC23\nPiping just like current seat to be in: Free Range Pampas FR22.\nBoth from Edelman leather samples, he still is patient and feels this is between you and Edelman.\nThe Gulfstream is located at Newark , Signature and will be there for your crew to remove the seats any time between now and Friday, May 11th. Our paint slot is Monday May 14 start date.\nPlease let me know when you can remove the seats and I will get aircraft to the paint shop by Friday night.\nWe just returned from Paris , and will depart Wed night at 630pm to St. Thomas in Boeing.\nlet me know your thoughts?\nleather lead time? etc.  I believe Larry Morrison said G2 will be in paint for 4 to 5 weeks.\nAlso, can your QC provide a 337 or adjusted weight and balance for our flight to Canada with the seats removed, please have Jay or QC dept coordinate with Larry Morrsion for proper paper work.\nthanks,\nLarry Visoski\n \n\n\n\n\n\n\nSee what's free at AOL.com.","body_html":"<html><head><style type=\"text/css\"><!-- DIV {margin:0px;} --></style></head><body><div style=\"font-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;font-size:12pt\"><DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">please explain to eric, that the delay in fixing the interior, is costing me a great deal of time and dimunition in value of selling the plane. HE said he would stand behind the work and I expect him to do, so, he should check with his attnys if need be regarding responsibility. . It can't be mine. It is not my dissatisfaction.. it is obvious. to anyone. who sees it... WE await his proposal..<BR><BR>\n<DIV style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman, new york, times, serif\">----- Original Message ----<BR>From: \"LVJET@aol.com\" &lt;LVJET@aol.com&gt;<BR>To: JEEPROJECT@YAHOO.COM<BR>Cc: DKIESQ@aol.com; kellens@earthlink.net<BR>Sent: Tuesday, May 8, 2007 10:04:13 PM<BR>Subject: G2 leather update:<BR><BR><FONT id=role_document face=Arial color=#000000 size=2>\n<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=4>Jeffrey,</FONT></STRONG> see Eric's comments below, </DIV>\n<DIV>I plan on taking the Gulfstream to Paint shop Friday after seats are removed.</DIV>\n<DIV>Paint shop is located in London, Ontario Canada, 1 hour north west of NYC.</DIV>\n<DIV><STRONG><FONT size=3>Darren,</FONT></STRONG> I thought you should be aware of current updates with Eric Roth at IJI on leather for Gulfstream.</DIV>\n<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV></FONT><BR><BR><BR>\n<DIV><FONT style=\"FONT: 10pt ARIAL,; COLOR: black\">\n<HR style=\"MARGIN-TOP: 10px\">\nSee what's free at <A title=http://www.aol.com?ncid=AOLAOF00020000000503 href=\"http://www.aol.com/?ncid=AOLAOF00020000000503\" target=_blank rel=nofollow>AOL.com</A>. </FONT></DIV>\n<STYLE>\n<!--\n _filtered {font-family:Helvetica;panose-1:2 11 6 4 2 2 2 2 2 4;}\n _filtered {font-family:Tahoma;panose-1:2 11 6 4 3 5 4 4 2 4;}\n/* Style Definitions */\n p.MsoNormal, li.MsoNormal, div.MsoNormal\n\t{margin:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;font-size:12.0pt;font-family:\"Times New Roman\";}\na:link, span.MsoHyperlink\n\t{color:blue;text-decoration:underline;}\na:visited, span.MsoHyperlinkFollowed\n\t{color:blue;text-decoration:underline;}\nspan.EmailStyle18\n\t{font-family:Helvetica;color:blue;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none none;}\n _filtered {margin:1.0in 1.25in 1.0in 1.25in;}\ndiv.Section1\n\t{}\n-->\n</STYLE>\n\n<DIV class=Section1>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Dear Larry,</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Let me start off by saying that International Jet Interiors appreciated the relationship with JE &amp; company.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">We refurbished the GIIb using leather that JE had specified \u2013 not IJI.&nbsp; The seating upholstery came out great and the problem that I agree exists is the \u201cpuckering\u201d of the leather while in St. Thomas .</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">It is my strong opinion that this problem is somehow due to the high humidity level interacting with the leather causing this adverse effect.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">The seats looked great when we viewed them (post - St. Thomas ) at Teterboro , NJ .</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Further, the one single seat that has not left our building also looks great \u2013 no puckering \u2013 even after we put sandbags on the seats for over three hours to create the weight of a passenger.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">We have contacted and sent JE\u2019s photo\u2019s to Edeleman and have had numerous discussions with Kasthy \u2013 our Edelman representative.&nbsp; She assured me that the owners of the company as well as may others who could be instrumental in identifying the cause of the problem have all viewed JE\u2019s photo\u2019s.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Edeleman has about 100 sq. ft of this specific dye lot in stock and has sent it to the lab for testing.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">At this point Edelman has made no suggestion as to what the problem is and if they agree that it may be their leather.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Additionally, if it is their leather, they have not expressed any terms of financial recourse.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">The new leather that JE would like will take 2 weeks to manufacture.&nbsp; The piping color is \u201cin stock\u201d in a different leather type, but one that Edelman believes would work well as it is only the trim.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">I want to make sure that we are very clear as to everyone\u2019s position at this point as you have requested for us to remove the seats without identifying who will be financially responsible in compensating IJI to perform any work as desired by JE.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">I will work on special pricing to show my contribution in trying to resolve JE\u2019s dissatisfaction.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">I look forward to speaking with you tomorrow morning at 9:00.&nbsp; Hopefully by then Jay and Glenn will have had time to see if they have any weight and balance information on the GIIb to see if we removed the cabin single and double chairs, would the aircraft still fall within the envelope.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">We are making a very sincere effort to keep JE happy.</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=blue size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<DIV>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Sincerely,</SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=blue size=3><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: blue\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><STRONG><B><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Eric H. Roth</SPAN></FONT></B></STRONG><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><EM><I><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">President</SPAN></FONT></I></EM><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=blue size=3><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: blue\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\"><IMG id=_x0000_i1027 height=137 src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" width=173 align=baseline border=0></SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=blue size=3><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: blue\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><STRONG><B><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">International Jet Interiors</SPAN></FONT></B></STRONG><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">960 South Second Street</SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">Ronkonkoma</SPAN></FONT><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">, NY 11779</SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">631.737.5900&nbsp;&nbsp; Phone</SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">631.7371249&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Fax</SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=Helvetica color=#605937 size=2><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #605937; FONT-FAMILY: Helvetica\">516.857.6533&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cell</SPAN></FONT><FONT color=blue><SPAN style=\"COLOR: blue\"></SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=blue size=3><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: blue\">&nbsp;</SPAN></FONT></P>\n<P class=MsoNormal><FONT face=\"Times New Roman\" color=blue size=3><SPAN style=\"FONT-SIZE